## Remarks  
 <span data-ttu-id="7325e-103">每當.NET Framework Data Provider for SQL Server 發生伺服器產生的錯誤時，會建立這個類別。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="7325e-103">This class is created whenever the .NET Framework Data Provider for SQL Server encounters an error generated from the server.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="7325e-104">（用戶端錯誤會擲回為標準的 common language runtime 例外狀況。）<xref:System.Data.SqlClient.SqlException>一定會包含至少一個執行個體<xref:System.Data.SqlClient.SqlError>。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="7325e-104">(Client side errors are thrown as standard common language runtime exceptions.) <xref:System.Data.SqlClient.SqlException> always contains at least one instance of <xref:System.Data.SqlClient.SqlError>.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="7325e-105">訊息的嚴重性層級 10 或更少則僅供參考之用，並指出使用者已輸入的資訊中的錯誤所造成的問題。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="7325e-105">Messages that have a severity level of 10 or less are informational and indicate problems caused by mistakes in information that a user has entered.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="7325e-106">嚴重性層級 11 至 16 由使用者產生，並且可以由使用者更正。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="7325e-106">Severity levels from 11 through 16 are generated by the user, and can be corrected by the user.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="7325e-107">17 到 25 的嚴重性層級表示軟體或硬體錯誤。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="7325e-107">Severity levels from 17 through 25 indicate software or hardware errors.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="7325e-108">當層級 17 時、 18 或 19 的錯誤，就會發生，您可以繼續工作，但您可能無法執行特定陳述式。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="7325e-108">When a level 17, 18, or 19 error occurs, you can continue working, although you might not be able to execute a particular statement.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="7325e-109">當嚴重性層級為 19 或低於 19 時，<xref:System.Data.SqlClient.SqlConnection> 仍保持開啟。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="7325e-109">The <xref:System.Data.SqlClient.SqlConnection> remains open when the severity level is 19 or less.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="7325e-110">伺服器時的嚴重性層級 20 或更高，通常會關閉<xref:System.Data.SqlClient.SqlConnection>。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="7325e-110">When the severity level is 20 or greater, the server ordinarily closes the <xref:System.Data.SqlClient.SqlConnection>.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="7325e-111">但是，使用者可以再次開啟連線，然後繼續進行。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="7325e-111">However, the user can reopen the connection and continue.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="7325e-112">在這兩個情況中，<xref:System.Data.SqlClient.SqlException> 皆由執行該命令的方法所產生。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="7325e-112">In both cases, a <xref:System.Data.SqlClient.SqlException> is generated by the method executing the command.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="7325e-113">SQL Server 所傳送的警告和參考用訊息的相關資訊，請參閱[Database Engine 事件和錯誤](/sql/relational-databases/errors-events/database-engine-events-and-errors)。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="7325e-113">For information about the warning and informational messages sent by SQL Server, see [Database Engine Events and Errors](/sql/relational-databases/errors-events/database-engine-events-and-errors).</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="7325e-114"><xref:System.Data.SqlClient.SqlException>類別會對應至 SQL Server 的嚴重性。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="7325e-114">The <xref:System.Data.SqlClient.SqlException> class maps to SQL Server severity.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="7325e-115">以下是關於處理例外狀況的一般資訊。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="7325e-115">The following is general information on handling exceptions.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="7325e-116">您的程式碼應該攔截例外狀況以防止應用程式損毀並允許向使用者顯示相關的錯誤訊息。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="7325e-116">Your code should catch exceptions to prevent the application from crashing and to allow displaying a relevant error message to the user.</span></span>  <span data-ttu-id="7325e-117">您可以使用資料庫交易來確保資料一致，不論用戶端應用程式 （包括當機） 中發生的動作。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="7325e-117">You can use database transactions to ensure that the data is consistent regardless of what happens in the client application (including a crash).</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="7325e-118">System.Transaction.TransactionScope 或 BeginTransaction 方法 （在 System.Data.OleDb.OleDbConnection、 System.Data.ODBC.ODBCConnection 和 System.Data.SqlClient.SqlConnection） 等功能可確保一致的資料不會理會例外提供者所引發。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="7325e-118">Features like System.Transaction.TransactionScope or the BeginTransaction method (in System.Data.OleDb.OleDbConnection, System.Data.ODBC.ODBCConnection, and System.Data.SqlClient.SqlConnection) ensure consistent data regardless of exceptions raised by a provider.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="7325e-119">交易可以失敗，因此攔截失敗和重試交易。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="7325e-119">Transactions can fail, so catch failures and retry the transaction.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="7325e-120">請注意.NET Framework 4.5 中，該開頭<xref:System.Data.SqlClient.SqlException>可以傳回內部<xref:System.ComponentModel.Win32Exception>。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="7325e-120">Note that beginning with  .NET Framework 4.5, <xref:System.Data.SqlClient.SqlException> can return an inner <xref:System.ComponentModel.Win32Exception>.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="7325e-121">例外狀況類別的.Net Framework 資料提供者報告提供者特有的錯誤。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="7325e-121">The exception class of a .Net Framework data provider reports provider-specific errors.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="7325e-122">例如 System.Data.Odbc 有 OdbcException、 System.Data.OleDb 有 OleDbException，而且 System.Data.SqlClient 具有 SqlException。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="7325e-122">For example System.Data.Odbc has OdbcException, System.Data.OleDb has OleDbException, and System.Data.SqlClient has SqlException.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="7325e-123">最佳的層級的錯誤詳細資料，攔截這些例外狀況，並使用這些例外狀況類別的成員，以取得錯誤詳細資料。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="7325e-123">For the best level of error detail, catch these exceptions and use the members of these exception classes to get details of the error.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="7325e-124">除了提供者特定錯誤，.NET Framework 資料提供者類型可以引發 System.Threading.ThreadAbortException System.OutOfMemoryException 等的.NET Framework 例外狀況。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="7325e-124">In addition to the provider-specific errors, .NET Framework data provider types can raise .NET Framework exceptions such as System.OutOfMemoryException and System.Threading.ThreadAbortException.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="7325e-125">從這些例外狀況復原不可能。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="7325e-125">Recovery from these exceptions may not be possible.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="7325e-126">不正確的輸入可能會造成要引發的例外狀況，例如 System.ArgumentException 或 System.IndexOutOfRangeException 的.NET Framework 資料提供者類型。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="7325e-126">Bad input can cause a .NET Framework data provider type to raise an exception such as System.ArgumentException or System.IndexOutOfRangeException.</span></span>  <span data-ttu-id="7325e-127">在錯誤的時間呼叫的方法可能會引發 System.InvalidOperationException。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="7325e-127">Calling a method at the wrong time can raise System.InvalidOperationException.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="7325e-128">因此，在一般情況下，撰寫例外狀況處理常式，以攔截任何提供者特定的例外狀況，以及從 common language runtime 例外狀況。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="7325e-128">So, in general, write an exception handler that catches any provider specific exceptions as well as exceptions from the common language runtime.</span></span>  <span data-ttu-id="7325e-129">這些可以是層級，如下所示：</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="7325e-129">These can be layered as follows:</span></span>  
  
```csharp  
try {  
   // code here  
}  
catch (SqlException odbcEx) {  
   // Handle more specific SqlException exception here.  
}  
catch (Exception ex) {  
   // Handle generic ones here.  
}  
  
```  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="7325e-130">或：</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="7325e-130">Or:</span></span>  
  
```csharp  
try {  
   // code here  
}  
catch (Exception ex) {  
   if (ex is SqlException) {  
      // Handle more specific SqlException exception here.  
   }  
   else {  
      // Handle generic ones here.  
   }  
}  
  
```  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="7325e-131">您也可針對.NET Framework 資料提供者的方法呼叫失敗在執行緒集區執行緒，並在堆疊上沒有使用者程式碼。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="7325e-131">It is also possible for a .NET Framework data provider method call to fail on a thread pool thread with no user code on the stack.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="7325e-132">在此情況下，並且使用非同步方法呼叫時，您必須註冊<xref:System.AppDomain.UnhandledException>來處理這些例外狀況，並避免應用程式當機事件。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="7325e-132">In this case, and when using asynchronous method calls, you must register the <xref:System.AppDomain.UnhandledException> event to handle those exceptions and avoid application crash.</span></span>  
  
   
  
